**Q3.**  
The loop adds `inc` to `x` until `x` becomes `inf`.  
If `inc` is **positive**, the loop will eventually reach `inf` (after `inf/inc` iterations), so the program will **not** print “Done”.  
If `inc` is **zero**, `x` never changes and the loop runs forever.  
If `inc` is **negative**, `x` decreases and the loop also runs forever.

Hence **no positive finite input** will cause the program to print “Done”.  
The only way to see “Done” is to supply an input that makes the loop body **never execute**, i.e. an input that is **not positive**.  
For example:

- `inc = 0.0`  
- `inc = -1.0`

Both satisfy the requirement. [end of text]


